President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Illinois and has ordered federal aid to help with recovery efforts after a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred between January 31 and February 3, 2011. The federal funding will be available for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in various counties. Assistance will also be provided for emergency protective measures and hazard mitigation statewide. Gregory W. Eaton has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.